PUH-BrianMartell The Hubble tension remains a full-blown crisis as of January 2026. Local measurements (supernovae, cepheids, TRGB, JWST confirmations) consistently yield H₀ ≈ 73–76 km/s/Mpc. Early-universe probes (Planck CMB, ACT final data, DESI BAO) give H₀ ≈ 67–68 km/s/Mpc. The discrepancy is now >5σ in many analyses — no sign of resolution in ΛCDM, with some calling it evidence for new physics. PUH resolves this elegantly without new fields: the tension is real and expected due to directional cosmology from the rebound jet.
